The paper deals with a problem related to computational geometry, specifically the problem of finding a maximum-cardinality subset of points in general position in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper mentions approximation algorithms, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
